  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this pilot study is to collect preliminary clinical data related to the safety
      and preliminary clinical benefits of non-invasive vagal nerve stimulation with the AlphaCore™
      device for the relief of acute bronchoconstriction due to asthma.

      Up to 30 subjects who meet all inclusion/exclusion criteria and consent to participate in the
      study may be enrolled at up to 5 investigational (study) sites. The study sites are clinic
      settings capable of treating any potential complications of bronchoconstriction, an acute
      exacerbation of asthma, and any emergencies associated with use of the investigational
      device.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Subjects will be screened, consented and enrolled at the first visit. Subjects will return to
      the second visit where they are experiencing shortness of breath and will be treated with the
      alphacore. Breathing and vital signs will be measured before, during and after the
      stimulation. The study is concluded on the third visit, 7 days later.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
